iiitb:advanced_wireless_communications_lab a edu:Lab ;
    rdfs:label "Advanced Wireless Communications Lab" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "The \"Advanced Wireless Communications Lab\" is focused on developing next generation wireless communication technologies (e.g., MIMO technologies, Cognitive Radio technologies, Cooperative Communication, Physical Layer Security, Energy Harvesting Networks, Green Communication, mmWave communication systems, and Intelligent Reflecting Surfaces). Emphasis will be on building new wireless communication systems and development of new technologies with their performance analyses. We focus mostly on physical layer concepts. Through MS by Research, and Ph.D programs, students will get trained in designing new communication technologies from scratch with detailed mathematical analysis, as applicable. This will lead to skill development which will satisfy academia and industry needs altogether. Motiv" ;
    edu:people "['About us']" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/labs/advanced-wireless-communications-lab/about-us-2" .

iiitb:ahana_pradhan a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Ahana Pradhan" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "ahana [dot] pradhan [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Ahana Pradhan has completed her M.Tech. and Ph.D. (dual degree) from CSE, IIT Bombay in 2018 (Specialization: Petri nets and Workflow Systems, Supervisor: Dr. Rushikesh K. Joshi), and has recently completed her postdoctoral research (2023-2025) from CDS, IISc. (Specialization: Databases, Supervisor: Dr. Jayant R. Haritsa). She has 6 years of industry R&D experience (2017-2023) in database technologies from Huawei India. She completed her bachelor'" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/dr-ahana-pradhan" .

iiitb:ajay_bakre a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Ajay Bakre" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "ajay [dot] bakre [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Education :Ph.D. (Rutgers University, NJ) Dr. Ajay Bakre joined IIIT-B and COMET Foundation as Professor of Practice in July, 2024. He has over 27 years of industry experience in startups, corporate research labs and product groups of multinational corporations. His areas of expertise include Scalable and Resilient Distributed Systems, Storage Systems Architecture, Distributed Object Storage and High-Availability Unified Storage Platforms, Wireless N" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/ajay-bakre" .

iiitb:amit_chattopadhyay a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Amit Chattopadhyay" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "a [dot] chattopadhyay [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Education :Ph.D. (University of Groningen) Dr. Amit Chattopadhyay received his Ph.D degree in \"Certified Geometric Computation\" from Johann Bernoulli Institute (JBI) of Mathematics and Computer Science at University of Groningen in the Netherlands in Jan 2011. After receiving his Ph.D he worked as a postdoctoral fellow at Universite Catholique de Louvain in Belgium, at University of Leeds in UK  and at IISc, Bangalore. He holds an M.Tech degree " ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/amit-chattopadhyay" .

iiitb:amit_prakash a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Amit Prakash" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "Amit Prakash is a Professor at the International Institute of Information Technology Bangalore (IIITB). He serves as the Convenor of IIITB’s Centre for Accessibility in the Global South (CAGS); he has also been involved in establishing and managing the Institute's Centre for IT and Public Policy (CITAPP) and E-Health Research Centre (EHRC). His interests lie in Information Systems and Public Policy, particularly as they intersect with development sectors such as public health & nutrition, educat" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/amit-prakash" .

iiitb:amrita_mishra a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Amrita Mishra" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "amrita [dot] mishra [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Amrita Mishra received the B.Tech. degree in electronics and communication engineering from Amrita School of Engineering, Amrita Vishwa Vidyapeetham, Coimbatore, India, in 2011 and her M.Tech - PhD Dual degree from the Department of Electrical Engineering, IIT Kanpur, Uttar Pradesh, India, in 2018. Her Ph.D. thesis explored applications of sparse signal processing for channel estimation in coded wireless systems, millimeter wave communication, MIM" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/amrita-mishra" .

