iiitb:ascend_studio a edu:Lab ;
    rdfs:label "Ascend Studio" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "The Robotics lab at IIIT-B focuses on theoretical and experimental work in the areas of Mobile Robots, such as Ground Robots and Quadrotor aircraft (drones), as well as robotic manipulators. As Robotics is an interdisciplinary field, concepts from Computer Vision, Algorithms, Feedback Control, Embedded Systems, to name a few, are widely applied in the problems currently being tackled in the lab. Some of the problems of current interest are Cooperative Collision Avoidance in a swarm of robots, both in 2-D and 3-D space; Algorithms for Collaborative Task Execution; Human-Robot interaction; GPS-denied Navigation, to name a few. The lab is equipped with an Indoor Robotics Studio consisting of 5 ground robots and 3 drones. The Robotics Lab is also closely associated with and houses the Remote L" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/labs/ascend-studio/ascend-studio" .

iiitb:ashish_choudhury a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Ashish Choudhury" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "ashish [dot] choudhury [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Dr. Ashish Choudhury received his MS (by Research) and Ph.D. degree from Indian Institute of Technology, Madras in 2006 and 2010 respectively. After his Ph.D. he worked as a visiting scientist at Indian Statistical Institute Kolkata for a year and then as a research assistant for two years at University of Bristol. His research interest include theoretical cryptography, with specialization in cryptographic protocols. My Profile: Check myhomepag" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/ashish-choudhury" .

iiitb:aswin_kannan a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Aswin Kannan" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "aswin [dot] kannan [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Education :Ph.D. (Pennsylvania State University) Aswin Kannan holds a Doctorate from Pennsylvania State Univ., US State (Advisor: Dr. Uday Shanbhag, Dec. 2014), a Masters from Univ. of Illinois at Urbana Champaign, US (May 2010), and a Bachelors from College of Engineering Guindy, India (May 2008). Prior to joining IIIT Bangalore, he worked for Humboldt Universitaet zu Berlin in the Mathematics department as a faculty member (Group Leader, 2021-202" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/aswin-kannan" .

iiitb:badrinath_ramamurthy a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Badrinath Ramamurthy" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "badrinath [dot] r [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Education :Ph.D. (Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, NY USA) Badrinath joined IIIT-Bangalore from Ericsson Research, Bangalore where he was working between 2014 and 2021. He was part of a team that deals with the machine reasoning technologies in AI. This includes technologies such as AI planning and Semantic web. His areas of application have been zero-touch automation and IoT. Prior to Ericsson he was with HP, Bangalore, between 2003 and 2014, wher" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/dr-badrinath-ramamurthy" .

iiitb:balaji_parthasarathy a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Balaji Parthasarathy" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "Education :Ph.D. (University of California Berkeley) The State andLate Industrialisation; Innovation Policies and Regional Economic Development; Civil Society Institutions, Frugal/Social Innovation; Multinational Enterprises, Small and Medium Enterprises; Computer Software and New Media Industries;  Political-Economy of E-Governance and Information Access; E-Waste Flows; Urbanism, Urbanisation and \"Smart\" cities; The Platform Economy Policy reports, working papers, and theses Other writings, sel" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/balaji-parthasarathy" .

iiitb:balakrishnan_ashok a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Balakrishnan Ashok" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "Education :Ph.D. (University of Massachusetts Amherst) Postdoctoral work at the Lorentz Institute for Theoretical Physics, Leiden, The Netherlands, and at the Materials Research Centre, Indian Institute of Science, Bangalore. Prior to joining IIITB in July, 2012, he was an Assistant Professor at the Central University of Hyderabad since April, 2007. Complex Systems, Nonlinear dynamics, Biomechanics & Biology-motivated problems, Theoretical Soft Condensed Matter  & Polymer Physics Know more:Compl" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/balakrishnan-ashok" .

