iiitb:radar_sensing_lab a edu:Lab ;
    rdfs:label "Radar Sensing Lab" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "Radar Sensing Lab works in the broad spectrum of applications of radar. In particular, the team currently works on problems specific to automotive, medical, and communication applications. The availability of off-the-shelf radars has enabled us to explore new problems and their applicability. We work closely with the industry and are open to collaboration with universities and government organizations. The team and infrastructure are progressively growing to accept challenging problems and solve them. We look forward to motivated students who are inclined towards research (MS by Research and Ph.D.) in such domains. Interested candidates shall email their resume with their Statement of Work tovinod.reddy@iiitb.ac.in. © 2026 IIIT-Bangalore. All Rights Reserved" ;
    edu:people "['Updates!', 'Thumbs Up:', 'Congratulations', 'Congratulations']" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/labs/radar-sensing-lab/radar-sensing-lab" .

iiitb:raghuram_bharadwaj a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Raghuram Bharadwaj" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "raghuram [dot] bharadwaj [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Raghuram Bharadwaj received his Ph.D. from the Indian Institute of Science (IISc), Bangalore, in 2022. His main research interests are in the areas of Reinforcement Learning, Deep Learning, Machine Learning, Game theory, and Multi-agent learning. He received the best student paper award at the International Joint Conference on Neural Networks (IJCNN) 2022 in Padova, Italy. His Ph.D. thesis focuses on developing reinforcement learning algorith" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/raghuram-bharadwaj" .

iiitb:research_programmes a edu:Program ;
    rdfs:label "Research Programmes" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:description "both full-time and part-time (for working professionals) The Master of Science degree is intended for mature students who wish to learn and perform research in a supportive academic environment. It is awarded upon successful completion of a graduate-level The Master of Science degree is intended for mature students who wish to learn and perform research in a supportive academic environment. It is awarded upon successful completion of a graduate-level 26/C, Opposite of Infosys Gate 10Electronics City Phase 1, Hosur RoadBengaluru - 560100 © 2026 IIIT-Bangalore. All Rights Reserved" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/academics/research-programmes" .

iiitb:sachit_rao a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Sachit Rao" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "Dr Sachit Rao obtained his Master's and Ph.D. degrees in Mechanical Engineering from the Ohio State University. His specialization is in the area of Control Systems and Theory with an emphasis on Sliding Mode Control. He has over 3 years of post-doctoral experience working in the areas of control of electric machines, swarms of dynamic agents, and guidance laws for tactical interceptors. He also has 3 years of industrial experience working for an Indian robotics company. Prior to joining IIITB, " ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/sachit-rao" .

iiitb:sakshi_arora a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Sakshi Arora" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "sakshi [dot] arora [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Interests:Analog ICs, PMICs, Open-source Analog ICs, Neuromorphic Circuits, Hardware for Mental Health Industry-University Effort: ADEC:Analog Design Evolution Collective Ph.D. (2013) Stanford University, High-frequency dc-dc converter, Advisor: Prof. Bruce Wooley, Co-advisor: David Su, Ph.D. 2017-2019 Tech Lead, Touch Hardware Group, Apple Inc., Cupertino, California 2014-2017 Hardware Design Engineer, Apple Inc., Cupertino, California 2013-2014 A" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/sakshi-arora" .

iiitb:sanghasri_mukhopadhyay a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Sanghasri Mukhopadhyay" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "sanghasri [dot] m [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Education :Ph.D (Université Grenoble Alphs, France & Université Savoie Mont Blanc, France) I completed myMaster’s in Applied MathematicsfromSouth Asian University, New Delhi (2014–2016), where I was awarded theGold Medalfor securing thefirst rankin my batch. I then pursued my doctoral research as afull-time PhD scholaratUniversité Grenoble Alpes (2016–2019)andUniversité Savoie Mont Blanc (2019–2020), France, earning aPhD in Energy and Process Engine" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/sanghasri-mukhopadhyay" .

iiitb:sanju_ahuja a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Sanju Ahuja" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "sanju [dot] ahuja [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Sanju Ahuja is an Assistant Professor at IIIT Bangalore. She holds a Ph.D in Design from IIT Delhi, and a B.Tech in Mechanical Engineering from IIT Delhi as well. She did her postdoc at the Inria Centre at Université Côte d'Azur, France. She is a human-computer interaction (HCI) researcher, and primarily studies dark patterns and usability violations on the web – which are designed to influence users to spend more time, money and share more personal" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/sanju-ahuja" .

iiitb:saumya_shankar a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Saumya Shankar" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "saumya [dot] shankar [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Saumya received her Ph.D. in Computer Science and Engineering from the Indian Institute of Technology Bhubaneswar in 2024. Prior to defending her thesis, she joined the University of Auckland, New Zealand, as a research associate, later transitioning to a postdoctoral role. Her research interests include formal methods and software engineering, with a particular focus on runtime verification and enforcement. Her work has been published in notable" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/saumya-shankar" .

iiitb:shiva_kumar_malapaka a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Shiva Kumar Malapaka" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "Dr.Shiva Kumar Malapaka worked for his Ph.D at the Max-Planck Institute for Plasma Physics, Garching, München and got his degree from University of Bayreuth, Bayreuth, Germany, in 2009. His thesis is on ' Simulations of Three Dimensional Magnetohydrodynamic Turbulence', where in he studied a property known as 'inverse cascade of magnetic helicity'. His Postdoctoral experience includes work at University of Colorado, Boulder, USA, UPMC, Paris, France, University of Leeds, Leeds, UK, TIFR-TCIS, Hy" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/shiva-kumar-malapaka" .

iiitb:shrisha_rao a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Shrisha Rao" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research "Shrisha Rao received his Ph.D. in computer science from the University of Iowa, and before that his M.S. in logic and computation from Carnegie Mellon University.  He is a full professor at IIIT-Bangalore. Dr. Rao was an ACM Distinguished Speaker from 2015 to 2021, and is a Senior Member of the IEEE.  He is also a life member of the American Mathematical Society and the Computer Society of India. Dr. Rao is on the editorial board ofPLOS ONE, and was previously on the boards ofSādhanāandThe Knowl" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/shrisha-rao" .

iiitb:shubha_krishnamurthy a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Shubha Krishnamurthy" ;
