    edu:research "shubha [dot] krishnamurthy [at] iiitb [dot] ac [dot] in Shubha Krishnamurthy is an Assistant Professor at IIIT Bangalore. She holds a PhD in Information Systems from the Indian Institute of Management Bangalore and was a post-doctoral fellow at IIIT Bangalore in the AI Innovation and Inclusion Initiative (A4I) project. Her doctoral research focuses on digitalization in the healthcare domain, examining IS adaptations in remote care delivery processes and their impact on health outcomes. Her resea" ;
    edu:source "https://www.iiitb.ac.in/faculty/shubha-krishnamurthy" .

iiitb:software_engineering_and_analysis_lab_seal_iiit_b a edu:Faculty,
        foaf:Person ;
    rdfs:label "Software Engineering and Analysis Lab (SEAL), IIIT-B" ;
    edu:belongsTo iiitb:iiitb ;
    edu:research """All mathematical aspects of software engineering, with specific interest on testing, 
formal verification and software specification. I also have research interests in 
concurrency theory, logic, automata theory and formal methods for avionics. History
 of computing, diversity in computing and intellectual property rights are other 
 areas of interest.""",
        """My research interests lie in formal methods and software engineering,
        with a particular focus on dynamic runtime verification. I have worked
        on runtime enforcement of regular properties expressed as automata under
        memory constraints, frameworks for timed properties using timed
        automata, enforcement of real-valued signals in reactive systems with
        Signal Temporal Logic, and compositional approaches for enforcing
        multiple properties. To demonstrate th""",
        "Research Interest :Software Engineering, Verification & Validation of Embedded Systems, Internet of Things Ganesha is currently working with Samsung R&D Institute India - Bangalore as a Chief Engineer and responsible for certification 	      of IoT devices. He has done his M. Tech in Computer Science and Engineering from NMAMIT Nitte (2009 – 2011) & B.E in Computer                  Science and Engineering from Vivekananada College of Engineering & Technology Puttur (2005 – 2009). Prior to joinin",
        "Research Interest :Verification & Validation of AI Systems, Safe AI, Adversarial Machine Learning, Formal Verification Sayak is currently working with Siemens Technology and Services as an Intern (Technical) to test and validate real-world AI-enabled systems.                  Prior to joining IIIT-Bangalore, he has worked at Tata Consultancy Services, Kolkata for the duration of 2022 to 2023.                  He has completed his B. Tech in Applied Electronics and Instrumentation Engineering fro",
        """Research Interest:Software Architecture, Reverse Engineering,
      Object-Oriented Analysis and Design. Ms. Aira is currently pursuing her Masters by Research at IIIT-B. She has worked for HCL Technologies Ltd prior to pursuing her research. Her other interests include playing basketball, music, and writing. Courses taken till now:Concrete Mathematics, Software Testing,
      Program Analysis.""",
        "Research Interest:Software Testing and Verification, Formal Methods in Software Engineering, Model-Based Testing for Web Services,Type Systems and Program Analysis Pranita is an MS student at IIIT Bangalore in the Department of Computer Science, working under the Software Engineering and Analysis Lab. Prior to joining IIIT Bangalore, she worked for two years at Cognizant as a Test Automation Engineer, gaining hands-on experience in software testing and verification. Beyond academics, she enjoys ",
        """Sujit's interest broadly lie in the formal aspects of software engineering. He is particularly interested in applying formal 
			techniques to improve the productivity of software engineers in various engineering domains. The domains he has worked in are: Sujit's current research efforts are in the development of advanced techniques of testing embedded software systems, formal specification of web-applications, and specification based testing of web-applications.""" ;
    edu:source "https://sealiiitb.github.io/people/aira.html",
        "https://sealiiitb.github.io/people/ganesha.html",
        "https://sealiiitb.github.io/people/meenakshi.html",
        "https://sealiiitb.github.io/people/people.html",
        "https://sealiiitb.github.io/people/pranita.html",
        "https://sealiiitb.github.io/people/saumya.html",
        "https://sealiiitb.github.io/people/sayak.html",
        "https://sealiiitb.github.io/people/sujit.html" .

